summary:
We prove that bounded solutions to degenerate parabolic double-phase problem modelled upon \[u_t-\dv(|
a u|^{p-2}
a u+a(x,t)|
a u|^{q-2}
a u)=-\dv(|F|^{p-2}F+a(x,t)|F|^{q-2}F)\,, \] where a nonnegative weight $a$ is $α$-Hölder continuous in space and $	frac α2$-Hölder continuous in time, have locally higher integrable gradients for the sharp range of exponents $p<q\le p+α$.
